{
  "doc_id": "41056",
  "text": "Sidhu et al [CITATION_1] reported a 72-year-old female with severe dyspnea and shock 7 days post bioprosthetic MVR who had a decline in platelet count with a positive heparin-induced thrombocytopenia (HIT) antibody assay; TTE and TEE both showed large immobile thrombi involving the left atrium and the mitral valve prosthesis. She underwent redo MVR with a mechanical prosthesis, but later died of multiorgan failure.",
  "correct_citation": {
